gomodel:SYNGO_2711  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.5: \"Decreased dendritic spine density and mEPSC amplitude in the DG of Arf4+/- mice compared to WT mice.\"\nFig.6: \"Expression of Arf4 in brain of 4.5-month-old mice and in primary neurons, and the effect of Arf4 overexpression on dendritic morphology.\"\nFig.7: \"Arf4 overexpression promotes dendritic spine development in mouse primary neurons.\"\nFig.8: \"Overexpression of constitutively active Arf4 (Arf4-Q71L) promotes dendritic spine development to a greater extent that Arf4-WT.\"\nFig.9: \"Knockdown of Arf4 by shRNA reduces spine density in mouse primary neurons.\"\nFig.12: \"Arf4 overexpression rescues spine loss in apoE4-expressing primary neurons.\". Experimental description: - \"Genotype of Arf4+/- mice ...\"\n- \"Mixed hippocampal and cortical neuron cultures were prepared from E18-19 mice...\"\n- \"HA-tagged human wildtype Arf4 was a gift from JD Lee \"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-22" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2711" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

